<scriptment id="17000" point="sakaguchi" localizationstatus="original" fictionaldate="2011-06-08" status="final" >
	<part>
		<narration>Yuki and Nozomi are walking down the street. They cross a man dumping tomes in a generic garbage collector lit ablaze.<comment>The player is able to continue walking and ignore what's happening here.</comment></narration>
		<line id="1000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Who is that?</line>
		<line id="2000" speaker="nozomi" voicelang="ja">He looks familiar.</line>
		<line id="3000" speaker="sakaguchi" voicelang="ja">Hello!</line>
		<narration>Nozomi stops and tilts her head at him.</narration>
		<line id="4000" speaker="nozomi" voicelang="ja">Hey, what's going on here?</line>
		<line id="5000" speaker="sakaguchi" voicelang="ja">My apologies. I'm an unsought guest in this wood.</line>
		<line id="6000" speaker="sakaguchi" voicelang="ja">After I dump these notes, I'll be on my way out of Tokyo.</line>
		<line id="7000" speaker="nozomi" voicelang="ja">Out?</line>
		<line id="8000" speaker="sakaguchi" voicelang="ja">I no longer wish to work in an industry wherein there is The Group.</line>
		<condition>
				<narration>Yuki is still standing there.</narration>
				<line id="9000" speaker="sakaguchi" voicelang="ja">I heard about what you did, Mademoiselle.</line>
				<line id="10000" speaker="sakaguchi" voicelang="ja">Realize that The Group cannot be destroyed by anger or hatred.</line>
				<line id="11000" speaker="sakaguchi" voicelang="ja">This is your story, Mademoiselle.</line>
				<line id="12000" speaker="sakaguchi" voicelang="ja">The Group's latest has met its lowest North American point-in-sale.</line>
				<line id="13000" speaker="sakaguchi" voicelang="ja">The era in which Japan rules the American game industry is ending.</line>
		</condition>
	</part>
</scriptment>